    <p class='chart-description'>New York is recycling more, up from a diversion rate of 21% in 2009 to 23% in 2018, but certain districts have regressed in their recycling habits over the past decade. The slack has hindered the Department of Sanitation's dreams of contributing zero waste by 2030.</p>
